<dl id="n36034a"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n36" href="#n36034a">N36 (VI.B.29)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n36all.htm#n36034a"> 34(a)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> yellow sands / Gillmerton</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">the village of <mark>Gilmerton</mark> (pop. 1482) which used to supply Edinburgh with <mark>yellow sand</mark>, when sanded floors were a feature in the humbler class of houses. <small> &ldquo;EDINBURGH&rdquo; <a name="EBED" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#EBED"><cite title="source">Encyclopaedia Britannica</cite></a>, 11th edit. (1911) 940c</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
